# Performance Rules

## Bundle Optimization
- Code split by route/feature (dynamic imports)
- Tree-shake unused exports
- Lazy load non-critical components
- Avoid barrel exports that prevent tree-shaking

## React Specific
- Use React.memo() for expensive pure components
- Use useMemo/useCallback for expensive computations and stable references
- Virtualize lists with 50+ items (react-window, react-virtuoso)
- Avoid inline object/array/function creation in JSX props
- Use React.lazy() + Suspense for route-level splitting

## Data Fetching
- Paginate API responses (never fetch unbounded lists)
- Cache responses where appropriate
- Debounce search inputs (300ms)
- Avoid N+1 query patterns
- Use SWR/React Query for client-side caching

## Images & Media
- Use WebP/AVIF format
- Provide responsive srcset/sizes
- Lazy load below-fold images
- Set explicit width/height to prevent CLS

## Core Web Vitals Targets
- LCP < 2.5s (largest contentful paint)
- INP < 200ms (interaction to next paint)
- CLS < 0.1 (cumulative layout shift)
